thinproxy (0.1.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Reject non-numeric ACL prefix lengths.
  * Stop forcing RST on accepted client sockets so HTTP error
    bodies reach the client.
  * Re-validate identity in event_loop to avoid an fd-reuse race.
  * Close all inherited fds in DNS child, not just below MAX_FDS.
  * Reject obs-fold and Transfer-Encoding+Content-Length combinations
    as request-smuggling vectors.
  * Treat write()=0 as a closed connection in the relay path.
  * Bound-check dr.addrlen before passing to connect().
  * Pre-scan -f with getopt so combined flag forms work.

 -- Renaud Allard <renaud@allard.it>  Sun, 03 May 2026 08:54:01 +0000

